---
import MainLayout from "../layout/MainLayout.astro";
import Icon from "../components/Icon.astro";
import SectionLabel from "../components/SectionLabel.astro";
import Button from "../components/Button.astro";
import Reveal from "../components/Reveal.astro";

const title = "About | Abhilash Kumar Panda";
const seoTitle = "About | Abhilash Kumar Panda";
const seoDesc = "From institutional finance reconciliation to production AI at London Stock Exchange Group — the story behind the work.";
---

<MainLayout title={title} seoTitle={seoTitle} seoDesc={seoDesc}>
  <section class="pt-32 md:pt-40 pb-24">
    <div class="max-w-content mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-20">
      <Reveal>
        <SectionLabel index="Origin" label="Story" />
        
        <h1 class="font-display text-headline md:text-display text-text-primary max-w-4xl">
          Why financial AI built by someone who lived it works differently.
        </h1>
      </Reveal>
      
      <div class="mt-12 max-w-prose space-y-6 text-body text-text-body leading-relaxed">
        <Reveal delay="80ms">
          <p>In 2017, I joined State Street Global Advisory as a Reconciliation Analyst. Every day: Bloomberg Terminal, Refinitiv Eikon, SmartStream TLM. Reconciling 100+ managed pension fund portfolios — equities, derivatives, FX, post-trade settlement, corporate actions. The grinding, precise, high-stakes work of institutional asset management.</p>
        </Reveal>
        
        <Reveal delay="160ms">
          <p>Most people would see that as a detour before a "real" tech career. <span class="text-text-primary">I see it as the most important thing I ever did.</span> Because when I crossed over to data science at LSEG in 2019, I didn't just bring Python and statistics — I brought an intimate understanding of the data I was now being asked to automate.</p>
        </Reveal>
        
        <Reveal delay="240ms">
          <p>I knew why Korean regulatory filings were structured the way they were. I knew what made a broker report ambiguous. I knew which edge cases would break a production system in the third month, not the third day. <span class="text-text-primary">That knowledge is not in any dataset. You get it by living inside the domain.</span></p>
        </Reveal>
        
        <Reveal delay="320ms">
          <p>Nine years and £600K+ in delivered value later, the same pattern keeps repeating: the best financial AI comes from teams that combine deep market expertise with serious engineering. I've done both sides. Now I'm looking for the next stage in <span class="text-text-primary">teams building production AI for financial markets</span> — whether that's fintechs, exchanges, asset managers, or financial-services arms of global technology companies.</p>
        </Reveal>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 border-t border-border">
    <div class="max-w-content mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-20">
      <Reveal>
        <SectionLabel index="Career" label="Timeline" />
        <h2 class="font-display text-headline md:text-display text-text-primary">Three chapters</h2>
      </Reveal>
      
      <div class="mt-16 relative">
        <div class="absolute left-[15px] md:left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-px bg-border md:ml-[140px]"></div>
        
        {[
          {
            years: "2017 — 2019",
            role: "Reconciliation Analyst",
            org: "State Street Global Advisory",
            text: "Learned the language of institutional finance: reconciliations, settlements, corporate actions, and the edge cases that break models."
          },
          {
            years: "2019 — 2022",
            role: "Data Scientist",
            org: "London Stock Exchange Group",
            text: "Built NLP and ML pipelines for financial documents. Turned domain knowledge into automation."
          },
          {
            years: "2022 — Present",
            role: "Senior Data Scientist",
            org: "London Stock Exchange Group",
            text: "Leading GenAI and agentic systems for financial data extraction, RAG, and document intelligence."
          }
        ].map((entry, i) => (
          <Reveal delay={`${i * 80}ms`} as="article" class="relative grid md:grid-cols-[140px_1fr] gap-6 md:gap-12 pb-16 last:pb-0">
            <div class="flex md:block items-center gap-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-caption text-text-muted uppercase tracking-[0.12em] md:text-right">{entry.years}</span>
              <div class="md:hidden w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-text-muted"></div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="relative pl-10 md:pl-0">
              <div class="hidden md:block absolute left-[-49px] top-1 w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-text-muted"></div>
              <h3 class="font-display text-title text-text-primary">{entry.role}</h3>
              <p class="font-mono text-caption text-text-muted uppercase tracking-[0.12em] mt-1">{entry.org}</p>
              <p class="mt-4 text-body text-text-body leading-relaxed">{entry.text}</p>
            </div>
          </Reveal>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 border-t border-border">
    <div class="max-w-content mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-20">
      <Reveal>
        <SectionLabel index="Edge" label="Unfair Advantage" />
        <h2 class="font-display text-headline md:text-display text-text-primary">My unfair advantage</h2>
      </Reveal>
      
      <div class="mt-16 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {[
          { icon: "document", title: "Domain-first", text: "I understand the financial instruments, workflows, and failure modes of the systems I'm automating — before a single line of code." },
          { icon: "chart", title: "Commercially accurate", text: "My AI systems are optimised for business outcomes, not benchmark scores. £600K+ in delivered value is the only benchmark that matters." },
          { icon: "layers", title: "Full-stack AI", text: "From data extraction pipelines to agentic orchestration to LLM fine-tuning to LLMOps. I ship systems end-to-end." }
        ].map((a, i) => (
          <Reveal delay={`${i * 80}ms`} as="article" class="group p-6 rounded-xl border border-border bg-transparent hover:bg-surface hover:border-border-strong transition-all duration-200">
            <Icon name={a.icon} class="h-7 w-7 text-text-muted" size={28} />
            <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-border">
              <h3 class="font-display text-title text-text-primary">{a.title}</h3>
              <p class="mt-3 text-body text-text-body leading-relaxed">{a.text}</p>
            </div>
          </Reveal>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 border-t border-border">
    <div class="max-w-content mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-20">
      <Reveal>
        <SectionLabel index="Credentials" label="Education & Certifications" />
      </Reveal>
      
      <div class="mt-12 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <Reveal delay="80ms">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-title text-text-primary mb-6">Education</h3>
            <div class="space-y-6">
              <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-border">
                <p class="font-display text-body text-text-primary">PG Diploma, Finance & Operations</p>
                <p class="font-mono text-caption text-text-muted uppercase tracking-[0.12em] mt-1">ISME, Bangalore · 2015 — 2017</p>
              </div>
              <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-border">
                <p class="font-display text-body text-text-primary">B.Tech, Mechanical Engineering</p>
                <p class="font-mono text-caption text-text-muted uppercase tracking-[0.12em] mt-1">Silicon Institute of Technology, Odisha · 2010 — 2014</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </Reveal>
        
        <Reveal delay="160ms">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-title text-text-primary mb-6">Certifications</h3>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              {[
                { title: "PG Programme in Data Science", org: "INSOFE / Carnegie Mellon University", icon: "graduation" },
                { title: "Machine Learning in Production", org: "Andrew Ng · Coursera", icon: "book" },
                { title: "Complete MCP Developer Guide", org: "Udemy", icon: "wrench" },
                { title: "Six Sigma Green Belt", org: "KPMG", icon: "chart" }
              ].map(cert => (
                <div class="flex items-center gap-4 p-4 rounded-xl border border-border">
                  <Icon name={cert.icon} class="h-5 w-5 text-text-muted flex-shrink-0" size={20} />
                  <div>
                    <p class="font-display text-body text-text-primary">{cert.title}</p>
                    <p class="font-mono text-caption text-text-muted uppercase tracking-[0.12em] mt-0.5">{cert.org}</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </Reveal>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 border-t border-border">
    <div class="max-w-content mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-20">
      <Reveal>
        <div class="p-8 md:p-12 rounded-2xl border border-border bg-surface">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-text-primary mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span>
            <div>
              <h2 class="font-display text-title text-text-primary mb-3">Open to opportunities</h2>
              <p class="text-body text-text-body leading-relaxed mb-6 max-w-xl">Seeking senior IC and lead roles in fintech, exchanges, asset management, and financial AI teams worldwide. If you're building production AI in financial markets and want someone who actually understands both sides, let's talk.</p>
              <Button href="mailto:abhilash.k.panda@gmail.com" variant="primary">
                <Icon name="mail" class="h-4 w-4" size={16} />
                abhilash.k.panda@gmail.com
              </Button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </Reveal>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
